results.deck: Years-old gamehouse that has produced such timeless classics as Wheel of Fortune: Featuring Vanna White for the NES, Wheel of Fortune, featuring Vanna White, for the Super Nintendo, and Wheel of Fortune, featuring Vanna White, for the Nintendo 64. Gametek was founded in Miami Florida in the earl 1990s.
results.description: Gametek's inital offering consisted of home computer versions of popular game shows such as Wheel of Fortune or Jeopardy, later on Gametek would extend their genre boundaries and release games of any genre. In 1995 Gametek announced Robotech: Crystal Dreams, a game based on the anime Robotech , for the Nintendo 64. The game recieved much intrest due to it's long development cyclye, eventually being cancled when Gametek filed for Bankruptcy in 1997. After Gametek's bankruptcy some of its assets were aquired by Take Two Interactive. Gametek is as of now, defunct.
